comments: Powell (DAL) firms up in Branham's (SAS) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the pick.
Johnson (SAS) legally contests Hardy's (DAL) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Mamukelashvili (SAS) brings his right hand to Bullock's (DAL) back and marginal contact occurs as Mamukelashvili releases away from the defender.
Powell (DAL) legally contests Mamukelashvili's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
Branham (SAS) brushes Green's (DAL) side after he receives the ball and the contact is marginal.
Branham (SAS) moves laterally into Hardy's (DAL) path and body contact occurs that affects Hardy's driving shot attempt.
Johnson (SAS) establishes himself in Bullock's (DAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

Bullock (DAL) holds his left hand out and marginal contact occurs with Johnson's (SAS) head at the start of his dribble. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Bullock (DAL) brings his right hand to the ball and dislodges it from Johnson (SAS) after the gather. The arm contact following the dislodge is considered incidental.
Green (DAL) releases his pass and moves to, rather than through, Graham's (SAS) space and the ensuing contact is marginal. Incidental foot to foot contact causes both players to fall to the floor.
Mamukelashvili (SAS) initiates contact with Wood's (DAL) wrist, which affects his play at the basket.
Branham (SAS) splits his feet at the start of his dribble.
Kleber (DAL) establishes himself in Branham's (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Mamukelashvili (SAS) initiates contact to Hardy's (DAL) body, which affects his SQBR during his dribble.
Johnson (SAS) engages with Green (DAL) as the players come together during the pick and the contact is marginal.
Wood (DAL) initiates contact with Jones' (SAS) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Graham (SAS) establishes himself in Wood's (DAL) path and absorbs the marginal contact at the end of the drive.
Wood (DAL) goes to, rather than through, Graham (SAS) when marginal contact occurs as Wood spins and changes directions.
Jones (SAS) avoids making contact with Wood (DAL) and legally contests his jump shot attempt

Mamukelashvili (SAS) briefly extends and retracts his hands from Kleber's (DAL) body and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal. Kleber proceeds to come together with Hardy (DAL) and incidental contact occurs.
Green (DAL) legally contests Jones' (SAS) shot attempt at the basket.
Jones (SAS) commits a take foul on Hardy (DAL). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of the fourth quarter and overtime.
Johnson (SAS) and Kleber (DAL) engage and disengage as the screen is set and the contact is marginal.
Mamukelashvili (SAS) establishes himself in Kleber's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the screen.

Replay review of the shooting foul called on Kleber (DAL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Kleber jumps from point A to point B and delivers body contact that affects Johnson's (SAS) layup attempt at the basket.
Johnson (DAL) crosses the plane of the free throw line prior to his free throw attempt coming into contact with the rim. Possession is correctly awarded to Dallas.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Kleber's (DAL) inbound pass goes out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to SAS.
Kleber (DAL) and Johnson (SAS) engage and disengage during the inbound and the contact is marginal.
Kleber (DAL) legally contests Johnson's (SAS) lob attempt at the basket.
